Philippine Stocks: Megawide Construction, San Miguel

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-08T09:03:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/mrc-allied-nickel-asia-san-miguel-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index decreased 22.90, or 0.5
percent, to 4,375.85. The measure retreated for a second day
after closing at a record on July 5.  Megawide Construction Corp. (MWIDE PM) climbed 5.1 percent
to 11.04 pesos, a record close since the shares started trading
on Feb. 18. The company’s board approved a plan to issue up to 3
billion pesos ($70 million) in fixed-rate notes, a stock
exchange filing showed.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  , largest Philippine food and
drinks company, increased 1.3 percent to 127.50 pesos, the
highest close since April 12. The company will likely reach an
agreement on an overseas acquisition in August, President Ramon
Ang said in a mobile-phone message yesterday, without
elaborating.  SMC Global Power Holdings Corp., the company’s power unit,
plans to hold an initial share sale this year and banks have
been “invited” to arrange the initial public offer, Ang said
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
